## SECTION 7 — PROGRESSIVE-DISCLOSURE GUARD INTEGRATION

When domain skill intent is detected, cross-reference the subject term with this bridge before loading skill guides:

1. If term is `CONFIRMED` in this brain db, load skill manifest + triggers + one primary loading-rule (no deep search needed).
2. If term is `INFERRED`, load skill manifest + triggers, then conditionally load nested files based on loading-rules.
3. If term is `UNKNOWN`, invoke progressive-disclosure router-contract guard: ask one clarifying question or route to deep-discover with search.

This coordination reduces token waste by confirming domain context early.

## SECTION 8 — CONFIDENCE RULES

When performing a brain lookup, classify the result:

| Confidence | Criteria |
|---|---|
| `CONFIRMED` | Term is explicitly defined in this brain db with a source citation |
| `INFERRED` | Term matches a pattern in this brain db but is not directly cited |
| `UNKNOWN — SEARCH REQUIRED` | Term not found in brain db; proceed to Step 2 (workspace grep/semantic search) |

> If brain lookup returns `CONFIRMED`, you MAY skip Step 2 (SEARCH) and proceed directly to Step 4 (SYNTHESIZE), citing this brain db as authority. Always still perform Step 3 (CROSS-REFERENCE) to enrich with live workspace details.

